parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the forward collision warning system and automatic emergency braking can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Failure of the forward collision warning system to alert the driver
failure of the automatic emergency braking system to engage

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls after starting
the vehicle stalls while driving
the vehicle shuts off and on repeatedly
the vehicle has difficulty staying running.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unstable engine RPM and vibration can cause loss of control, increased stopping distance, and accidents, especially when merging onto a highway or climbing an incline.
symptoms: The engine RPM jumps around
the vehicle vibrates or shakes
the vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate
the accelerator pedal must be depressed all the way to the floorboard to achieve acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission hesitation and shudder can cause the vehicle to accelerate slowly or unpredictably, leading to potential accidents or near-misses, especially when merging or avoiding obstacles.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or shudders when accelerating
fails to downshift
or accelerates slowly
especially when merging or turning; the transmission shudders in multiple gears
including first and second gear; the manual gear lever develops play
making it difficult to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and flywheel can cause the transmission to shudder, making it difficult to shift gears, and potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission shudders
especially when starting from a dead stop; the clutch and flywheel need to be replaced prematurely; the manual gear lever develops play
making it difficult to shift gears.
